<p>In the admin area, the "Add" button points here. Click it!</p>
<blockquote><p>The controller must return a response (<code>null</code> given). Did you forget to add a return
  statement somewhere in your controller?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yep, a great explosion!</p>
<h2 id="instantiating-the-form-object">Instantiating the Form Object <a class="headerlink" href="render-form-bootstrap#instantiating-the-form-object" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>To create the form object, add <code>$form = $this-&gt;createForm()</code>. This is a shortcut method
in the base <code>Controller</code> that calls a method on the <code>form.factory</code> service. That's
my friendly reminder to you that <em>everything</em> - including form magic - is done by
a service.</p>
<p>To <code>createForm()</code>, pass it the form type class name - <code>GenusFormType::class</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="b01ef61f94">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-39" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
